verse_part: in the flower of their age.
And it shall come to pass,
I will also make an end.
the women that stood by her
As soon as ye be come
And when they were come down
to the top of the house,
that I may send thee away.
and it shall come to pass,
And when he had made an end
that we may put them to death.
that as soon as he had made an end
within as it were an half
of the things which should have been utterly destroyed,
and it shall come to pass,
had put the battle in array,
when he had made an end
and they gave them in full tale
And [when] thou hast stayed three days,
and it shall come to pass,
And it shall come to pass,
that thou mayest make known unto me
and as soon as ye be up early
where those that were left behind
that they could not go over
and I will bring thee down
And when he had brought him down,
whom they had made also to abide
